project | AI | ai | DIGITAL PHOTO AI | BETA | Project developed to easily provide portrait/document digital photo to satisfy distances constraints such as:
- distance chin to crown
- frame width and height in px and in physical mm
- resolution
The system detects the face in the image and crop it basing on the input params which rappresents the constraints described earlier.
USE CASE:
Any photo preparation for VISA applications, document ID photo, etc.. | https://github.com/bacobax/digital_photo_ai

project | AI | ai | AUDIO OVERFIT IMPAINTING | ONGOING | A Generative AI approach to impaint missing parts of an musical audio signal using techniques such as:
- MAE
- Diffusion models
- Adversarial Training
The main characteristic is that this system is only allowed to train on a single mp3 trace and learn to "fill in the gaps" for that one song | https://github.com/bacobax/audio_overfit_impainting

project | AI | ai | FEW SHOTS CLIP ADAPTATION | TERMINED | This project is about finding solution on top of the state of the art, to either improve or create a method to improve accuracies of CLIP on classification task over SEEN and UNSEEN classes.
In this project me and my teammate worked on top of CoCoOp paper's implementation and tried different ablation-style methods such as:
- KL distillation
- Adversarial Domain Generalization + clustering
- Data augmentation | Seen classes: 79.01%, Unseen classes: 75.46%, Harmonic mean: 77.20% | https://github.com/bacobax/few-shot-CLIP-adaptation

text: project | AI | ai | PROMPT ENGINEERING THESIS | TERMINED | This thesis explores the power of prompt engineering in large language models, with a goal of human-AI interaction optimization for software engineering tasks. Through comprehensive evaluation and analysis, it is indicated that the research work presented herein makes a significant improvement in AI-assisted tasks in the context of code refactoring and user interface optimizations using models OPENCHAT, MISTRAL, and LLama3. The paper develops a framework for effective prompts that would enhance the performance and reliability of AI systems in practical applications, further contributing toward understanding AI application in technology- driven environments. | https://github.com/bassi-uni/tesi

meta.title: PROMPT ENGINEERING THESIS
meta.summary: This thesis explores the power of prompt engineering in large language models, with a goal of human-AI interaction optimization for software engineering tasks. Through comprehensive evaluation and analysis, it is indicated that the research work presented herein makes a significant improvement in AI-assisted tasks in the context of code refactoring and user interface optimizations using models OPENCHAT, MISTRAL, and LLama3. The paper develops a framework for effective prompts that would enhance the performance and reliability of AI systems in practical applications, further contributing toward understanding AI application in technology- driven environments.
